reviews.text: Wonderful 'off the beaten path' museum with hundreds of windmills. Also has a great toy train village set up that my young kids could have watched for hours (trains and windmills were apparently brought to the west around the same time). Worth the time to come here, give yourself about 1-1.5 hrs to go through it all.

This museum is great if you are interested in windmills. It is in an 80000 square foot modern steel building that is heated and air conditioned. Its clean and well lit, but rows of old windmills, some admittedly awesome miniature doll houses and some model train exhibits to walk through are the only thing out there. There are no interactive displays to keep young children occupied. There is a gift shop and soft drinks available.This museum is what it is.
OK, how much can you learn about windmills?  ALOT.  This museum was just fascinating.  People of every age will love it.

Awesome! The size and quantity of windmills  mostly inside coupled with a very expansive train layout and miniature doll houses plus more. I was apprehensive initially about going but would return again if ever in the area.
I was very impressed with the museum.  I loved the amazing train display.  The staff were very friendly and helpful.

Wonderful gallery that showcases and promotes local artists in Lubbock. It is the hub of the First Friday Art Trail (you guessed it, the first Friday evening of every month). Thousands of people come out, there are food trucks and live music. Super cool!
I love LHUCA! it's a place where you can visit alternative realities and pretend to enjoy space candy (ceramic)
This expanding venue is a delight.  The varied exhibitions display a variety of  styles and artists as well as participatory activities.

The first Friday walks are a great date idea. With food trucks, friends, and new people to meet it'll keep your interest.
There are delightful art exhibits to view as well.

Nice gallery with local artists on display.   Inside is the Firehouse theater for plays and musical performances.  I even had a friend get married there.  This is the center for the First Friday Art Trail that occurs the first friday of the month.  Worth checking out if you like art.

I have officiated 2 wedding in the chapel and I have to say it is a beautiful place to start your marriage! The chapel is quaint and warm feeling. The grounds are gorgeous. My kids really enjoy the pumpkin walk in the fall. If your looking for an awesome place to go for a stroll, check this place out.
Such a beautiful place. Had daughters first birthday pictures done and they came out beautiful
We love this park. The Lubbock Parks and Recreation team do a wonderful job on the Annual Pumpkin Trail. Love it every year.
Visit on a sunny  day and enjoy. Wary spring and fall is good photo opportunity
Love this place and all its hidden wonders through the years.
Very nice park. My niece and I ate lunch there. Beautiful!
Beautiful grass, very well kept especially for a girls JUSA soccer match.
This place was better than Disney world for us! The locals tell you everything you need to know!! Truly magical!!
Good park. Quiet and places for kids or bbqs. The equipment is old, so one star off.
It's a really great and safe place.

Very interesting place. Museum inside was informative and well put together. Went on the walking trails available, and had a really good time. Views were rather pretty. Lots of historical and geological facts are presented here, along with cultural speculations of the prehistoric indigenous peoples of the Lubbock area.

Pleasant walking trails of various lengths, short boardwalk for young and old with descriptions of plant life, short and easy path around the lake. Far off views of prairie dogs on the longer gravel and dirt path.  No shelter areas on the longer walk. Be prepared for windy conditions. 

The museum is small, showcasing extinct animal bones and ancient flint points. Large interesting dioramas and text on waves of migrating people who may have exterminated their predecessors or assimilated with them.  

Dating method of B.P. beginning in 1950 and also beginning at some other unspecified time (?) were somewhat confusing on a few exhibits.  As was the vague implication  that calendars are a recent invention. Various methods of calculating time have been around for a very long time. The exhibits would be more interesting using different types of calendars.
The museum was really interesting and the statues outside are awesome. It's really hard to imagine a 14 foot tall mammoth untill it's right there in front of you.
Great hiking trails. Good way to experience the native landscape of the south plains.
Quiet - wonderful place to visit. Great displays!
Free and fun! So many different exhibits and activities. Enough to keep the kids busy for half a day. I would bring a stroller and good walking shoes.

Your portrayal of Native American art and the West in general wreaks of colonial undertones.  Native American exhibit shows a lack of cultural understanding.  Puebloan tribes and other Southwestern peoples such as the Navajo (Dine), are NOT the same and should not be grouped together.  They have a conflicted past.  Additionally, your display of Lubbock history is shamefully white.  There is no mention of the contributions of African Americans or Latino Residents.  Lubbock segregation is void from the conversation.  This shows in my opinion, poor taste and perpetuates colonial and archaic ideologies.  Get with the times.

It's free so you can't complain. I enjoyed the fossils and the paintings, especially the mammoth  and the Norman Rockwell. My girlfriend liked the red dress exhibit. Next time I'm in Lubbock I'll check out the Ranching Heritage Museum

Recently went to the ranching heritage candle light event and it was amazing. It was so cool In seeing the actors dress up and bring the historical building to life. I’ve also been here on the regular days and it’s so fascinating In learning about the history of each house at the museum!! Def it’s a must. You can also enjoy the inside of museum and they have a lot of cool displays about the Native American Cherokee and the cowboys. Also if you are looking to see the 6666 barn it’s a must!! It’s free to visit but you can also donate a few bucks if you can!! Enjoy!

Candlelight At The Ranch is a wonderful tradition that me and my family look forward to each year. It's an experience that is heartwarming plus it teaches the younger generation what life was like back then. It's awesome and I hope this continues for years to come!

Really wasn't ready for how good this place was. I have to admit I had my doubts, but when I went inside and looked at the menu I was very surprised. Everything that came out of the kitchen looked amazing. I had the fish and chips dinner, I was so impressed. The fish was freshly battered and fried. The burgers were huge and looked just as great. The prices were more than reasonable. Overall a wonderful experience. Highly recommend. Looking forward to returning.

I definitely think it depends on what you order! The burgers were good with fresh toppings however the mashed potatoes were as dry and flavorless! The side salad was decent. Burgers worth a try otherwise not impressive.
Had to wait for someone to help us even though we were the only ones there. My order was brought out wrong. Had to wait for someone again to fix it but once it was fixed the food was good.
My husband and I forgot about how good and easy this place was! On days we dont know what to do for lunch a quick Jumbo Joe's is great! Even have online ordering to make it fast
We ordered burgers and tots with a couple of side orders of fried mushrooms. Food was delicious 👌. Didn't take long to get our order through the drive up
This is an awesome place , wish they were open year round!
Has great tamales and tortillas!
Closed until October 2018
Wish it was open all year
The tamales are really good
Awesome customer service. The food is delicious. I had the chicken fried chicken. It was very good. I would recommend Cotton Patch to all my friends.
We ordered an "apetizer".  Never got it.  The food was cold.  Ordered catfish basket.  Not catfish.   Ordered blat.  Extra crispy bacon.  Bacon was barely cooked.   Wong eat there again
Haven’t been in years. What a great experience!!  Food and service were great. My family and mulled will be back.

We had a wonderful experience with Cotton Patch yesterday, as we always have in the past.  We had quick, friendly service and great food.  We went for lunch, about 11:30.  The only negative thing was that our friend wanted to order the daily special and it wasn't ready.  It should have been ready to order as soon as the restaurant opened.  But he thoroughly enjoyed what he ordered instead.

We went yesterday on Sunday.  It was busy and the staff showed no care.  The manager seemed overwhelmed.  We left after being there an hour and twenty-five minutes including a 15 minute wait time.  We ordered mac and cheese, a cheese burger, chicken fried steak, and grilled shrimp.  There was no excuse to sit there for over an hour and not have food.   We left.  Take some time to acknowledge your guest, fill their drinks, apologize.  Be courteous and don't just keep taking orders if you can't fulfill the ones already placed.

Original Italian food. There's are several spicy options on the menu, while I enjoy it, that's generally something I'm not looking for in my Italian food. It's personally my favorite Italian restaurant in Lubbock. Service is generally good and friendly. They have lunch options if your not looking to spend an arm and leg. My one criticism is bread, when you go to a nice Italian place you expect great bread, not here, just ok.

Went to dinner here tonight, it was a perfect cozy atmosphere for a cold and cloudy night. Service was great, everything came out quickly. We split the Pasta for Lovers platter between our family of 4, it was plenty of food. We all loved the ravioli and the lasagna the most. We will definitely come back.

Yum, Yum , Yum was this Chicken Spaghetti, with large chucks chicken breast, bell peppers, sour cream sauce and marinara sauce over spaghetti noodles. Two large, warm pieces of garlic bread and a Caesar Salad rounded out my lunch feast..A total home run w/ this carry out 1st time treat for less than $15.00!. We've been here many times, both dine in and take out. The food is always delicious. The restaurant had great decor. It's generally pretty loud in there so it's no worry to bring our 3 year old.

Let me break it down for you. I travel a lot and I eat out a lot. Orlando's is pretty good, not great, but just pretty good. It's very busy, so yes it's loud. This is not a place for a romantic evening. I ordered several items, and the best thing was the mafia cheese dip and my margarita. It's time to update the recipes. We had 4 different pastas and all had the same, thick, heavy tomato sauce, and so it all tasted the same. I was not impressed. I first went to Orlando's 15 years ago, and at the time my young palate thought it was great. Now that I'm older and have experienced some great chefs and great restaurants, I would compare  the sauce here to something out of a jar. Don't get me wrong, the food is not bad, the place is clean, the menu items are fine, and everyone was very friendly. BUT the flavors of the menu item need to be revisited. Go lighter on the sauce, too thick and heavy, too must tomato paste or puree. Try a thinner sauce with fresher ingredients, more fresh basil, fresh herbs.

Orlando's was great. Busy, but i got right in, my waitress was friendly and accommodating. Food was delicious, my first time at there and i was not disappointed. The full size portion of ravioli was enough for me to get full, and have leftovers. Garlic toast was yum-o and great for scooping up leftover sauce. I really enjoyed it!

Fresh Mexican fare with a very wide variety of choices. A lot of custom "choose your own" combos as well as traditional house specials. Not too heavy like a lot of greasy Mexican cuisine.  They bring you cups and 3 different flavorful salsas right away. The service is excellent. Our server went above and beyond for us and was incredibly polite.
Good stop over for a quick appetizer and drink. Good attentive service and priced right. Don't pass on the chicken nachos, but what I expected, better than the menu description. Enjoy
Food was delicious but above all was the AMAZING service we received from our server Austin and the rest of Abuelos staff. He was so truly genuine and down to earth. All around a great experience.
Great food with great charm. Lots of options and large menu. I like the decor of the restaurant. Well worth the money

One of my favorite Mexican restaurants. The food is authentic and delicious. I come here every time I'm in town. The service is always prompt and friendly. Start with the jalapeno fritters with ranch dip...so good!  The 5 enchiladas platter is my husband's favorite. I love it all so I'm working through the menu.

Had a great experience for an early dinner at Ruby Tequilas.  Catarina was our amazing server and so efficient, smiley, and kind.   The margaritas were delicious and, although half price with happy hour, were perfect with tequila.  We shared the fajitas and had food leftover.  Fun!

Please stop using red raider wrecker as your tow service provider. This is putting Texas Tech students at a great risk of having their car towed in your parking lot. They charge the most they legally are allowed to charge to get your car out of impound. I and many others will no longer will be doing business with you if you continue to use them as your tow provider. They call themselves "red raider" and yet they screw over mostly Tech students You have give them the power to monitor your parking lot. This is something you should do yourselves. Your customers are being towed away. There are better tow company options that are more ethical then red raider wrecker. Please I implore you to change.

Please let us know who does handle the towing! this is still not fair to your customers that they are being targeted by Red Raider Wrecker and charged high fees. Please advocate to your landlords to switch to a towing company that doesn't call themselves "red raider" and yet tows mostly college kids and charges the highest they LEGALLY can charge. I understand if you are not responsible for the towing but you can advocate on behalf of your customers. Thank you

Our waiter Zachery was probably the best waiter ever. Ruby tequila's should feel privileged to have him as a part of their team representing their brand. We love coming here for the food the atmosphere and especially the dos-a-ritas. 😍😍 1-1-2017
ruby tequila's mexican kitchen

Amazing food, amazing service, and amazing prices. I got the calzone meal, and the 2 slices of pizza meal. Both lunch specials for $14 even. You can't beat that! It took about 5 minutes for them to turn out both meals and the waiters and cashier were incredibly welcoming and kind.

Overall this place has good eats and good people. It also touts it's status as the "best pizza in town" recipient for Lubbock, TX. I'm not sure if they're the best, but they certainly are great! I highly recommend this spot!
Super nice waitresses. 5 stars to them as well. And there food is delicious. .   Thanks guys. . .

We ordered from Door Dash. First time ever, and was quite satisfied. Alfredo was absolutely delicious, and my husband enjoyed his lobster ravioli. Rolls were cold, but nothing a quick zap in the microwave could not fix.
Very good food, nice staff, great environment, and amazing service. The cheesesteak meat had a great flavor, and the pizza dough was fresh.
Their calzones are the best! Good service!  I'll be returning!
The food was really good with organic ingredients and fresh veggies. The service was good too!
Calamari tough and chewy, spring mix laced with pieces that have turned, garlic shrimp over salted and shrimp mushy. Cucumber salad was ok.
Server was very nice but the food was certainly overpriced for its quality.. Pretty salty and also $10 for an appetizer of spring rolls seemed pretty outrageous..

Went here for a holiday party. The staff was great, lots of patience and super kind. The only thing that I liked from their food though was the steak, everything else tasted like they lost either spice rack.. totally bland..

Tiger rolls. This is the only place that has them anywhere and they are heavenly. Awesome outdoor seating overlooking the creek. Prices are higher than they should be but they cater to the tourist clientele/one time dinner guest. Very busy venue. Reservations recommended.

I absolutely love this fine establishment.  Top notch.  Somewhat pricy for lunch, but after tasting the chopped brisket sandwich, all I have to say is money well spent....It's a locally owned, cozy restaurant, with courteous and friendly service.  They are only open from 11am- until they sell out.   That means 2-2:30pm.
The meats are ridiculously delicious. Melt in your mouth, absolutely amazing.
This is the best little BBQ hideaway ever!!  I've been eating at this place for about 35 years & the food is always perfect!
Best spot for BBQ sandwiches in town!
Amazing food, good price, friendly people.
